menu "TrailCurrent FluidNC"

config FLUIDNC_USE_MOCK
    bool "Use mock backend (no real controller)"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, components/fluidnc/src/fluidnc_mock.c is compiled
        instead of the real protocol backend. The mock simulates motion,
        spindle ramp, and job progress so the touchscreen UI can be
        exercised on a bench without a FluidNC controller attached.

        Disable this to compile the real backend that talks to a FluidNC
        controller over WebSocket (default port 81 for FluidNC 3.x,
        80 for 4.x) or UART. The transport is selected at runtime via
        Settings → Machine → "Configure FluidNC Connection" and persisted
        in NVS via pendant_config.

endmenu
